                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d507">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2231/173a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gonzalez</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-17T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 17, 1937—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. Consul General at Guayaquil reports extensive changes in Ecuadoran import
                    tariff effective July 5.</p>
                <p>These changes should be considered before you present the list enclosed with the
                    Department’s instruction No. 244 of July 10.<note n="40" xml:id="d507fn40">See
                        bracketed note, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> Keep the Department
                    informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
